{
  "text": "Messaris [CITATION_1] explains that the two systems are structural and functionally distinct. Although being independent, the two systems are also interdependent in a way that a certain visual concept may be converted in a verbal etiquette and vice versa. A new interpretation to explain the interaction between the two systems is the metaphor of processing interactively in parallel. Redefining the notion of a \"primary\" system, and including visual communication as well as the verbal one, we can achieve a more complete analysis of the complexity of communication.",
  "citation_candidates": [
